        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 17 at 10:36AM EDT until August 17 at 11:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerous swimming conditions expected, especially by
late afternoon as winds shift to the north.

*Waves of 1 to 2 feet will build to 3 to 4 feet through the
day.

*Life-threatening rip and structural currents are expected.
Structural currents will be especially strong on the north
side of piers and breakwalls.

*A strong southward flowing longshore current is expected by
the afternoon.

* WHERE...In Indiana, Northern La Porte county. In Michigan,
Southern Berrien county.

* WHEN...From noon EDT /11 AM CDT/ today through this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
